ame":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Foliot was born about 1255, in Islington, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Foliot, was 31 and his mother, Margery Stuteville, was 32. He had at least 1 son with Audrey Falco. He died in 1312, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"Abt 1255–1312":"umbes 1255–1312","1249–1299":"1249–1299","1255–1312":"1255–1312","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1226–1299":"1226–1299","1225–1271":"1225–1271","1249":"1249","1226":"1226","1225":"1225","1312":"1312","Abt 1255":"umbes 1255","1245":"1245","1255":"1255","1299":"1299","1276":"1276","March 1299":"märts 1299","1271":"1271","Melbury Turberville Manor, Dorset, England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thornden, Windmill, Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tilney with Islington, Wisbech, Norfolk, England":"Islington, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1255–1312":"noin 1255–1312","1249–1299":"1249–1299","1255–1312":"1255–1312","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1276–Male":"1276–Kuollut","1226–1299":"1